<item>
            <title>[LU-10151] lnetctl gives the worst configration warning</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10151</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have one big complaint about lnetctl. Currently if you import an YAML configuration file with an error in it you get pretty much the same exact error message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;errno: -2&lt;br/&gt;
descr: &quot;missing mandatory parameters&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to know which line is actually broken instead of guessing what the problem is.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
